ift-invariant measures is obtained. The paper\ndescribes the structure of the space $\\cal H$ of numerical functions square\nintegrable with respect to the constructed shift and rotation-invariant measure\n$\\lambda $. The decomposition of the space $\\cal H$ into the orthogonal sum of\nsubspaces corresponding to all possible equivalence classes of bases is\nobtained. Unitary groups acting by means of orthogonal transformations of the\nargument in the space $\\cal H$ of square integrable functions are investigated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 26 Sep 2021 13:37:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-28"}
